What's wrong?

286
00:13:38,010 --> 00:13:38,960
Nothing.

287
00:13:39,630 --> 00:13:41,130
So all these common people

288
00:13:41,360 --> 00:13:43,000
don't have their own names.

289
00:13:43,910 --> 00:13:45,390
I didn't know "Passerby"

290
00:13:45,600 --> 00:13:46,360
was such a common surname

291
00:13:46,360 --> 00:13:48,200
in the capital.

292
00:13:49,320 --> 00:13:51,180
Quite an elegant surname indeed.

293
00:14:01,120 --> 00:14:01,910
Little one.

294
00:14:03,150 --> 00:14:04,720
Since your father's surname

295
00:14:04,720 --> 00:14:05,630
is Passerby,

296
00:14:06,460 --> 00:14:07,580
from now on,

297
00:14:07,790 --> 00:14:08,850
you shall be called

298
00:14:09,080 --> 00:14:10,030
Passerby Pancake.

299
00:14:10,030 --> 00:14:10,910
How's that?

300
00:14:11,440 --> 00:14:12,600
Thank you, Sir.

301
00:14:12,790 --> 00:14:13,600
Here,

302
00:14:13,600 --> 00:14:14,270
have this pancake.

303
00:14:14,270 --> 00:14:15,140
Take a big bite.

304
00:14:16,320 --> 00:14:19,180
Passerby C.
["C" sounds like "pancake" in Chinese]

305
00:14:24,480 --> 00:14:26,140
It's as if everything is stuck

306
00:14:26,150 --> 00:14:28,630
inside a fabricated, prewritten world.

307
00:14:32,960 --> 00:14:34,240
So handsome!

308
00:14:34,270 --> 00:14:36,030
Mr. Li's skills are truly extraordinary.

309
00:14:36,030 --> 00:14:38,030
My Lady, he's the one, definitely the one!

310
00:14:38,030 --> 00:14:38,910
Just days ago,

311
00:14:38,910 --> 00:14:40,910
weren't you
speaking highly of General Chu?

312
00:14:40,910 --> 00:14:42,480
Now you've switched sides.

313
00:14:42,870 --> 00:14:44,870
Before, I was just inexperienced,

314
00:14:44,960 --> 00:14:46,200
thinking that of all men in the world,

315
00:14:46,200 --> 00:14:47,630
only General Chu was the best.

316
00:14:47,630 --> 00:14:49,600
But now, after hearing
Miss's stories every day,

317
00:14:49,600 --> 00:14:52,130
I think Mr. Li
is even better than General Chu.

318
00:14:52,150 --> 00:14:54,150
You two are what we call daily followers,

319
00:14:54,150 --> 00:14:56,280
switching fandoms at the drop of a hat.

320
00:14:57,030 --> 00:14:58,120
Switching...

321
00:14:58,240 --> 00:14:59,200
But My Lady,

322
00:14:59,600 --> 00:15:01,240
what are your feelings

323
00:15:01,270 --> 00:15:02,360
toward Mr. Li now?

324
00:15:02,750 --> 00:15:04,270
If you like him,

325
00:15:04,510 --> 00:15:07,640
why not break off your engagement
and marry him instead?

326
00:15:08,710 --> 00:15:10,240
What are you talking about?

327
00:15:11,390 --> 00:15:12,270
Besides,

328
00:15:12,670 --> 00:15:14,150
the broken engagement plot

329
00:15:14,150 --> 00:15:15,410
is still a long way off.

330
00:15:15,480 --> 00:15:16,670
For now, I'd be counting my blessings

331
00:15:16,670 --> 00:15:18,750
if I could just slip out of

332
00:15:19,360 --> 00:15:21,240
Nan Heng's clutches safely.

333
00:15:21,550 --> 00:15:24,840
-My Lady.
-My Lady, please tell us more.

334
00:15:25,190 --> 00:15:26,230
Stop gossiping.

335
00:15:25,820 --> 00:15:30,720
[Slacker Escape Plan]

336
00:15:30,720 --> 00:15:37,200
[Li Shiliu]

337
00:15:50,720 --> 00:15:52,750
From what I know about Nan Heng,

338
00:15:52,750 --> 00:15:54,750
he's just an ambitious,

339
00:15:54,750 --> 00:15:55,870
ruthless,

340
00:15:55,870 --> 00:15:56,910
and heartless man.

341
00:15:56,910 --> 00:15:57,870
He commits all kinds of wicked deeds,

342
00:15:57,870 --> 00:15:58,910
falsely accuses loyal officials,

343
00:15:58,910 --> 00:15:59,870
and inflicts suffering upon women.

344
00:15:59,870 --> 00:16:01,240
He's a bad guy, you know?

345
00:16:01,260 --> 00:16:02,630
He kills without even blinking.

346
00:16:02,630 --> 00:16:04,150
Nan Heng has committed plenty of

347
00:16:04,150 --> 00:16:05,900
wicked deeds over the years, hasn't he?

348
00:16:05,900 --> 00:16:07,940
Nan Heng is a sinister villain.

349
00:16:07,960 --> 00:16:10,020
However, a protagonist like Nan Heng

350
00:16:10,610 --> 00:16:12,400
only cares about power and schemes.

351
00:16:12,400 --> 00:16:14,600
The people's lives mean nothing to him.

352
00:16:14,660 --> 00:16:15,680
Anyway,

353
00:16:15,960 --> 00:16:17,220
he's not a good person.

354
00:16:35,840 --> 00:16:36,630
Fugui!

355
00:16:37,080 --> 00:16:37,870
Come in!

356
00:16:41,550 --> 00:16:42,410
Your Highness.

357
00:16:42,560 --> 00:16:43,360
Let me ask you.

358
00:16:43,390 --> 00:16:44,390
Do you also think

359
00:16:44,720 --> 00:16:46,510
I am a person who only cares about power

360
00:16:46,510 --> 00:16:48,360
and ignores the lives of the people?

361
00:16:48,360 --> 00:16:49,820
What do you mean by "also"?

362
00:16:51,440 --> 00:16:53,520
No, it's impossible.

363
00:16:53,960 --> 00:16:55,710
Your Highness

364
00:16:55,910 --> 00:16:57,370
is known for your kindness

365
00:16:57,960 --> 00:16:59,080
and warmthâ€”

366
00:16:59,570 --> 00:17:01,270
truly a gentleman

367
00:17:01,490 --> 00:17:03,090
and a great hero of the realm.

368
00:17:04,720 --> 00:17:06,780
Do you really believe your own words?

369
00:17:11,510 --> 00:17:13,270
Since you don't believe it yourself,

370
00:17:13,270 --> 00:17:15,470
she certainly won't believe it either.

371
00:17:15,640 --> 00:17:16,440
She?

372
00:17:19,480 --> 00:17:21,750
Accompany me
to the Song Residence tomorrow.

373
00:17:21,750 --> 00:17:23,150
I have questions for her.

374
00:17:24,510 --> 00:17:25,640
Yes, Your Highness.

375
00:17:25,810 --> 00:17:29,510
[Song Residence]

376
00:17:30,880 --> 00:17:32,030
Twenty-five.

377
00:17:32,030 --> 00:17:33,310
Sixteen,

378
00:17:33,310 --> 00:17:34,270
seventeen.

379
00:17:36,200 --> 00:17:37,910
We're short on timber lately.

380
00:17:38,110 --> 00:17:39,470
To keep the project on schedule,

381
00:17:39,470 --> 00:17:41,070
we need to use materials sparingly.

382
00:17:41,070 --> 00:17:41,960
Remember, you twoâ€”

383
00:17:41,960 --> 00:17:44,270
everything here must be properly sorted

384
00:17:44,270 --> 00:17:45,590
and counted once a day,

385
00:17:45,590 --> 00:17:47,110
and any shortages reported right away.

386
00:17:47,110 --> 00:17:48,720
That's how we avoid mistakes.

387
00:17:48,720 --> 00:17:50,590
My Lady, you're impressive!

388
00:17:52,000 --> 00:17:53,330
I'm just helping Mr. Li.

389
00:17:54,070 --> 00:17:55,920
He's done so much for the people,

390
00:17:55,920 --> 00:17:57,440
so I should do my part too,

391
00:17:57,440 --> 00:17:58,160
right?

392
00:18:11,680 --> 00:18:13,010
What are you doing here?

393
00:18:15,110 --> 00:18:16,480
Is this how you treat

394
00:18:16,500 --> 00:18:18,920
the person who saved you

395
00:18:18,920 --> 00:18:21,180
from being charged with assassination?

396
00:18:21,860 --> 00:18:22,790
Your Highness,

397
00:18:22,790 --> 00:18:24,590
mind your gentlemanly conduct.

398
00:18:26,080 --> 00:18:28,080
I need to speak with Miss Song alone.

399
00:18:29,280 --> 00:18:30,640
Both of you, leave now.

400
00:18:32,240 --> 00:18:33,250
Your Highness,

401
00:18:33,270 --> 00:18:35,480
th-they don't know anything.

402
00:18:35,480 --> 00:18:36,800
Please don't frighten them.

403
00:18:36,800 --> 00:18:37,680
Besides,

404
00:18:38,060 --> 00:18:39,270
what is it

405
00:18:39,400 --> 00:18:41,200
that cannot be said in their presence?

406
00:18:41,200 --> 00:18:42,800
Why must we speak in private?

407
00:18:43,200 --> 00:18:43,960
Miss Song,

408
00:18:44,000 --> 00:18:45,430
His Highness suggests

409
00:18:45,590 --> 00:18:46,720
it might be a bit stuffy in here

410
00:18:46,720 --> 00:18:48,880
and perhaps the ladies
would appreciate some fresh air.

411
00:18:48,880 --> 00:18:49,680
Ladies,

412
00:18:49,790 --> 00:18:50,590
please.

413
00:18:57,420 --> 00:18:59,070
It's quite stuffy in here.

414
00:18:59,070 --> 00:19:00,800
I need to get some fresh air too.

415
00:19:01,710 --> 00:19:02,770
What are you doing?

416
00:19:05,710 --> 00:19:06,760
First question:

417
00:19:08,510 --> 00:19:09,610
To you,

418
00:19:10,270 --> 00:19:11,600
what kind of person am I?

419
00:19:14,560 --> 00:19:16,160
A truly admirable person.

420
00:19:18,310 --> 00:19:19,920
I want you to tell the truth.

421
00:19:21,110 --> 00:19:23,290
How is that not the truth?

422
00:19:23,310 --> 00:19:25,160
Even though Your Highness
has tried to kill me

423
00:19:25,160 --> 00:19:26,030
so many times,

424
00:19:26,030 --> 00:19:27,630
you always let me walk away.

425
00:19:27,690 --> 00:19:30,310
Such magnanimity,
rare even among top celebrities,

426
00:19:30,310 --> 00:19:32,250
combined with your remarkable foresightâ€”

427
00:19:32,250 --> 00:19:34,180
you're truly an admirable person.

428
00:19:36,960 --> 00:19:37,750
Fine.

429
00:19:38,960 --> 00:19:40,420
Then the second question:

430
00:19:41,400 --> 00:19:42,860
What is a "top celebrity"?

431
00:19:43,350 --> 00:19:45,080
What does "protagonist" mean?

432
00:19:45,550 --> 00:19:46,410
And what is this

433
00:19:46,550 --> 00:19:47,810
"script" you speak of?

434
00:19:50,600 --> 00:19:52,710
Everyone keeps asking me these questions.

435
00:19:52,710 --> 00:19:54,160
I-I really feel suffocated.

436
00:19:54,160 --> 00:19:55,680
I really need to go out and breathe

437
00:19:55,680 --> 00:19:57,070
some fresh air.

438
00:19:57,090 --> 00:19:59,200
I've searched through
all the books in the Wenyuan Library

439
00:19:59,200 --> 00:20:00,680
and questioned
all the scholars in the Hanlin Academy,

440
00:20:00,680 --> 00:20:02,740
yet no one knows anything about this.

441
00:20:05,370 --> 00:20:07,080
I was just saying it casually.

442
00:20:07,270 --> 00:20:08,790
Your Highness, seriously,

443
00:20:08,790 --> 00:20:11,440
why do you bother
remembering such trivial things?

444
00:20:11,440 --> 00:20:12,840
Just saying it casually?

445
00:20:13,400 --> 00:20:14,310
Once is fine,

446
00:20:15,310 --> 00:20:16,510
but what about twice?

447
00:20:16,640 --> 00:20:17,350
Three times?

448
00:20:17,350 --> 00:20:18,790
Four times? Five times?

449
00:20:19,680 --> 00:20:21,680
You once said I was the protagonist.

450
00:20:22,300 --> 00:20:24,310
Now you're calling me a top celebrity.

451
00:20:24,310 --> 00:20:25,110
You also mentioned that everything

452
00:20:25,110 --> 00:20:26,510
between us is part of some script rule.

453
00:20:26,510 --> 00:20:28,110
What does all that mean?

454
00:20:34,270 --> 00:20:35,070
Did I...

455
00:20:38,530 --> 00:20:39,870
Did I say that?

456
00:20:41,510 --> 00:20:42,310
Song Yimeng.

457
00:20:44,200 --> 00:20:45,600
I'm begging you to tell me

458
00:20:47,550 --> 00:20:49,510
what you're hiding from me.

459
00:20:55,440 --> 00:20:56,510
Your Highness,

460
00:20:56,720 --> 00:20:58,240
do you have any manners at all?

461
00:20:58,240 --> 00:21:00,400
How can you be so rude to a girl?

462
00:21:07,720 --> 00:21:08,510
Fine,

463
00:21:08,660 --> 00:21:09,990
I'll tell you today.

464
00:21:10,400 --> 00:21:11,880
A top celebrity
is someone with top traffic,

465
00:21:11,880 --> 00:21:13,240
and a script
is the foundation of a show.

466
00:21:13,240 --> 00:21:14,590
You, who only knows how to
use force when facing problems,

467
00:21:14,590 --> 00:21:15,070
who hasn't even learned basic

468
00:21:15,070 --> 00:21:15,790
English vocabulary,

469
00:21:15,790 --> 00:21:16,510
do you understand?

470
00:21:16,510 --> 00:21:17,440
Do you understand?

471
00:21:17,440 --> 00:21:18,500
Do you understand?

472
00:21:20,680 --> 00:21:22,050
You don't understand.

473
00:21:22,240 --> 00:21:23,310
Not only do you not understand,

474
00:21:23,310 --> 00:21:24,400
you kill without remorse,

475
00:21:24,400 --> 00:21:25,270
you slaughter the innocent.

476
00:21:25,270 --> 00:21:26,110
You don't really want to know

477
00:21:26,110 --> 00:21:27,440
what the real script is about.

478
00:21:27,440 --> 00:21:28,920
You just think I know more than you,

479
00:21:28,920 --> 00:21:30,480
you think I'm hiding everything from you.

480
00:21:30,480 --> 00:21:31,480
You want to control everyone,

481
00:21:31,480 --> 00:21:32,790
but you don't trust anyone.

482
00:21:32,790 --> 00:21:33,640
Am I right,

483
00:21:33,640 --> 00:21:34,500
Your Highness?

484
00:21:46,510 --> 00:21:49,200
Have I successfully mind-controlled him?

485
00:21:49,510 --> 00:21:50,310
Fine,

486
00:21:52,030 --> 00:21:53,830
you're right about everything.

487
00:21:53,960 --> 00:21:55,890
I did use force against you before,

488
00:21:58,000 --> 00:21:59,060
but let me tell you.

489
00:22:01,360 --> 00:22:02,940
Apart from this matter,

490
00:22:04,240 --> 00:22:06,300
I have never killed innocent people.

491
00:22:10,720 --> 00:22:12,270
I don't trust anyone,

492
00:22:13,070 --> 00:22:14,510
because no one has ever trusted me,

493
00:22:14,510 --> 00:22:15,750
not even you.

494
00:22:18,350 --> 00:22:19,160
I...

495
00:22:22,370 --> 00:22:23,500
You should know that

496
00:22:24,550 --> 00:22:25,590
things in this world

497
00:22:25,590 --> 00:22:28,210
are not what
they appear to be on the surface.

498
00:22:28,230 --> 00:22:30,760
What people say
isn't necessarily the truth.

499
00:22:30,990 --> 00:22:31,830
On the battlefield,

500
00:22:31,830 --> 00:22:33,270
it's kill or be killed.

501
00:22:33,510 --> 00:22:34,240
In the imperial court,

502
00:22:34,240 --> 00:22:36,450
it's even more
dangerous than the frontier.

503
00:22:36,450 --> 00:22:38,710
If I don't fight desperately to survive,

504
00:22:38,710 --> 00:22:40,910
then I'll be the one driven to a dead end.

505
00:22:47,640 --> 00:22:48,500
Song Yimeng.

506
00:22:49,920 --> 00:22:50,720
If

507
00:22:52,000 --> 00:22:53,800
you truly want to understand me,

508
00:22:54,950 --> 00:22:56,440
don't use your eyes.

509
00:23:24,270 --> 00:23:25,870
Who wants to understand you?

510
00:23:35,790 --> 00:23:37,050
Everyone present here

511
00:23:37,880 --> 00:23:40,550
is an expert in weapon forging.

512
00:23:41,830 --> 00:23:43,720
Our Chief Master has gone to great lengths

513
00:23:43,720 --> 00:23:45,850
to invite you all from the Huai region,

514
00:23:46,030 --> 00:23:47,360
spending several days,

515
00:23:47,440 --> 00:23:49,100
yet there's been no progress.

516
00:23:52,830 --> 00:23:55,630
You're making it
very difficult for me to explain.

517
00:23:56,700 --> 00:23:57,970
Mr. Shangguan,

518
00:23:58,480 --> 00:24:00,360
it's not that we're incompetent.

519
00:24:00,440 --> 00:24:02,880
The blades you want
must be forged from fine steel,

520
00:24:02,880 --> 00:24:04,920
but nowadays all the quality iron mines

521
00:24:04,920 --> 00:24:06,550
are under imperial control.

522
00:24:06,570 --> 00:24:08,550
To forge steel blades from ordinary iron,

523
00:24:08,550 --> 00:24:10,880
that's... that's simply impossible!

524
00:24:10,880 --> 00:24:11,310
Indeed.

525
00:24:11,310 --> 00:24:12,960
So if I provide you with fine iron,

526
00:24:12,960 --> 00:24:14,290
you could forge it then?

527
00:24:18,640 --> 00:24:20,160
Sir, what you don't know is

528
00:24:20,270 --> 00:24:22,110
the fine iron needs to be tempered

529
00:24:22,110 --> 00:24:23,640
before it can become steel.

530
00:24:23,750 --> 00:24:25,110
And this tempering method

531
00:24:25,110 --> 00:24:26,920
is known only to Lord Qianyu.

532
00:24:27,110 --> 00:24:28,350
In my youth,

533
00:24:28,550 --> 00:24:30,070
I was fortunate enough
to apprentice in the Qianyu Army

534
00:24:30,070 --> 00:24:31,800
under a blade-forging master.

535
00:24:31,830 --> 00:24:34,350
Even though he served
in the army for decades,

536
00:24:34,350 --> 00:24:36,680
he never obtained Lord Qianyu's formula.

537
00:24:37,000 --> 00:24:37,590
So...

538
00:24:37,590 --> 00:24:39,960
In the end, you still can't forge it.

539
00:24:41,880 --> 00:24:44,110
Guards! Take them away.

540
00:24:45,310 --> 00:24:46,110
Move along.

541
00:24:55,200 --> 00:24:56,200
What should we do?

542
00:24:57,400 --> 00:24:59,460
We'll have to target the Qianyu Army.

543
00:25:04,070 --> 00:25:06,510
Go to the South City
and tell the Chief Master

544
00:25:06,510 --> 00:25:08,310
that our mission remains unaccomplished,

545
00:25:08,310 --> 00:25:10,480
and we need to find
another way through Chu Guihong.

546
00:25:10,480 --> 00:25:11,270
Yes.

547
00:25:14,510 --> 00:25:16,380
Bravo! Bravo!

548
00:25:16,410 --> 00:25:18,200
Bravo! Bravo!

549
00:25:22,480 --> 00:25:23,270
General,

550
00:25:23,750 --> 00:25:25,480
what are they doing over there?

551
00:25:26,110 --> 00:25:28,400
Are they here to help
or just cause trouble?

552
00:25:28,400 --> 00:25:30,030
Chattering all day long,

553
00:25:30,070 --> 00:25:32,270
they're clearly
disrupting military discipline.

554
00:25:32,270 --> 00:25:33,510
Let them do their thing,

555
00:25:33,510 --> 00:25:34,720
we'll do ours.

556
00:25:35,200 --> 00:25:36,880
Only by completing this before next month

557
00:25:36,880 --> 00:25:38,110
can we help His Majesty

558
00:25:38,110 --> 00:25:39,000
and His Highness

559
00:25:39,000 --> 00:25:40,330
put their minds at ease.

560
00:25:42,550 --> 00:25:43,350
General,

561
00:25:43,680 --> 00:25:44,590
the Waning River Crescent

562
00:25:44,590 --> 00:25:46,390
is full of riffraff.

563
00:25:46,590 --> 00:25:47,400
When it comes to speed,

564
00:25:47,400 --> 00:25:49,050
we really can't compete with them.

565
00:25:49,050 --> 00:25:50,180
When the time comes,

566
00:25:50,880 --> 00:25:54,680
you won't really break off
your engagement with Miss Song, will you?

567
00:26:00,550 --> 00:26:02,210
That's none of your business.

568
00:26:02,270 --> 00:26:03,670
